Huawei has revealed its new MateBook X Pro laptop at MWC 2019. The updated version of the high-end notebook has a 13.9-inch LTPS FullView display with a resolution of 3,000 x 2,000 that is surrounded by ultra-thin bezels. The MateBook X Pro’s display also supports 10-point multi-touch and is powered by a discrete Nvidia GeForce MX250 graphics card with 2GB of GDDR5 memory. Connectivity options include 802.11ac dual-band Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.0, and Thunderbolt 3 for high-speed data transfer. Huawei’s refreshed MateBook X Pro also includes an 8th-generation Intel Core i5 or Core i7 processor and supports up to 16GB of LPDDR3 memory. The thin chassis of the device sports a sandblasted metallic finish and is available in Mystic Silver and Space Gray. There is currently no confirmed release date or pricing for the updated version of Huawei’s MateBook X Pro.